Hi Vitaliy,
Is this crash repeatable?
It looks like GParted crashed while reading file system information from your USB key. I assume your FAT16/32 file system is on your USB key on device /dev/sdc1.
Can you run the following command as root and attach the files. LC_ALL=C fsck.fat -n -v /dev/sdc1 1> fsck.out 2> fsck.err
Thanks, Mike Fleetwood (GParted Developer)
